what to do when you are very lonely what to do when you are very lonely ok i just got out of a painful 'relationship' had to let it go because well i refused to be a doormat but before he came into my life i was fine and just enjoying my everyday life however after it ended i suddenly felt lonely he basically awakened the feelings of being someone and caring about them and now i dont know what to do i'm really lonely i hang out with friends and try to keep busy but apparently it's not working i hate this feeling what you are going through is a very normal five stage process of loss in your life denial what's the first thing you do oh he's not so bad i can deal with it i really miss the good times anger he was such a jerk can you believe i put up with that crap for so long bargaining if i just tell myself that i can change this i can go back and fix it if i just depression oh god what am i going to do seems to be where you are now acceptance ok it's dead time to get on with my day i'll deal with this later one common definition of grief work is summarized by the acronym tear t to accept the reality of the loss e experience the pain of the loss a adjust to the new environment without the lost object r reinvest in the new reality tears will fall surround yourself with those whom love you unconditionally and those will let you talk through it have some tea start a fire even in the airconditioning and settle back for some chic flick movies that will rock you to remember what you really want from a good relationship you will come out of this this too shall pass Grief Narcissism A Course In Miracles About a Boy Harry Potter (character) Out-of-body experience Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Kodocha Anger management Cliff Richard Jiddu Krishnamurti Characters in the Smurfs Happiness Theory of conduct Sigmund Freud Hearing impairment Weight training Infantilism Skin of Evil (TNG episode) Milton H. Erickson Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Phoebe Halliwell Mojave people Shit 